content: On September 29, 1993, the Atlanta Braves clinched the National League East title, marking their second consecutive division championship under manager Bobby Cox. The Braves secured the title with a 4-3 victory over the New York Mets, thanks to clutch performances by players like David Justice and Fred McGriff. This victory was pivotal in establishing the Braves as a dominant force in the National League throughout the 1990s, leading to 14 straight division titles.
